cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a novel approach to determine the batch size in stochastic gradient descent methods, which is a common optimization technique used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with optimization and cost-sensitive approaches, which are relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper presents empirical results on popular classification tasks, which suggests relevance to categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
